                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/594a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-05T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 5, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>591. Your 1414, July 31, 4 p.m. The British Government has informally informed me
                    through the British Embassy here that the British Government has no intention to
                    close the Burma Road to shipments for China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
